The 2022 U.S. Open is ready to get underway on Thursday at The Country Club in Brookline, Mass. With a field full of intrigue, there is plenty worth watching. The course, full of storied history, was last in the spotlight in 2013 when the U.S. Amateur was played there. Prior to that, it was home to the unforgettable 1999 Ryder Cup. The U.S. Open tees off on Thursday, June 16, with the first featured group of Collin Morikawa, James Piot, and Jon Rahm teeing off at 7:18 AM ET. Three featured groups that include some of the top names in the sport will tee off in the span of roughly a half hour. The U.S. Open can be watched on NBC and USA Network. USA will air coverage of the first two rounds on Thursday and Friday and the final round on Sunday, with NBC airing the primary broadcast for each round beginning in the afternoon. Thursday, June 16: 9:30 a.m.-2 p.m. (USA); 2-5 p.m. (NBC); 5-7 p.m. (USA) Friday, June 17: 9:30 a.m.-4 p.m. (USA); 4-7 p.m. (NBC) Saturday, June 18: 12-8 p.m. (NBC) Sunday, June 19: 10 a.m.-12 p.m. (USA); 12-7 p.m. (NBC) Betting on the outright winner is no easy task, with every golfer in the field this year holding +1100 odds or longer. As of Wednesday evening, the top 10 golfers with the best odds of winning the tournament were: Rory McIlroy +1100 Justin Thomas +1200 Jon Rahm +1400 Scottie Scheffler +1400 Cameron Smith +2200 Patrick Cantlay +2200 Xander Schauffele +2200 Jordan Spieth +2500 Will Zalatoris +2500 Shane Lowry/Tony Finau +3300 The top names in the sport will be on display at the U.S. Open this year. Here is the full list of competitors and their tee times for the first round. (All times ET) * indicates teeing off on Hole 10 6:45 a.m.  – Michael Thorbjornsen, Erik Barnes, Matt McCarty 6:45 a.m.* – Fran Quinn, Callum Tarren, Hayden Buckley 6:56 a.m. – Matthew NeSmith, Patrick Rodgers, Travis Vick 6:56 a.m.* – Kurt Kitayama, Denny McCarthy, Sam Bennett 7:07 a.m. – Troy Merritt, William Mouw, Andrew Putname 7:07 a.m.* – Wyndham Clark, Bran